# Environment variables for Poetic Fiddle
#
# This is a TEMPLATE listing the variables the app expects — the contract to
# code against, not the secrets. It holds NO real values and is safe to commit.
#
#   • Local development: copy this file to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and fill
#     in real values from the Supabase dashboard (Project Settings → API).
#   • Deployed app: the running app reads these from Vercel's Environment
#     Variables (Project Settings → Environment Variables), NOT from this file.
#
# Never commit real values, and never place a secret (see tiers below) in the
# agents' workspace or a tracked file.
#
# Sensitivity tiers:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_*  — inlined into the browser bundle at build time. Safe to
#                    expose ONLY because Supabase Row-Level Security guards
#                    them. Anything under this prefix is effectively public.
#   everything else — server-only. Must NOT carry the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix and
#                     must never reach the browser or a committed file (AC88).
#
# The current Supabase project (URL/region) is recorded in
# docs/IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md §6.3.

# --- Supabase — auth, data/save, and SSR share pages (consumed from M4 on) ---

# Public. The project's REST/Auth endpoint, e.g. https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# Public. The "anon" / publishable key. Shipped to the browser; guarded by RLS.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# SECRET. The "service_role" key — it BYPASSES Row-Level Security, so it is
# server-only: never exposed to the browser, never committed. Only needed for
# privileged server operations; leave it unset until a milestone genuinely
# requires it (set it directly in Vercel, not in an agent's workspace).
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
